article.headline: Arkansas 94, Florida A&amp,M 55
article.story: FAYETTEVILLE, Ark. -- Rotnei Clarke and Marshawn Powell scored 14 points each as Arkansas defeated Florida A&M 94-55 on Wednesday night. The Razorbacks (16-9) took any suspense out of the game early, building a 43-6 lead and shooting 63 percent in the first half. Four players scored in double figures for Arkansas, which improved to 11-3 in non-conference games this season. Besides Clarke and Powell, Delvon Johnson finished with 13 points and Jeff Peterson added 10. Meanwhile, the Rattlers (11-15) connected on just 4 of 28 shots in the first half while falling to 0-2 against the Southeastern Conference this season. Florida A&M lost 76-37 at Alabama on Nov. 12. Avery Moore had 11 points for the Rattlers, who had their four-game win streak snapped.
